Four people were rescued from the inflatable vessel, which sank in waters near the town of Zarzis, but one is reported to have died in hospital later. The three Malians who were rescued said that they had set out from Zuwara in Libya.Â 

The country is a main departure point for migrants hoping to reach Europe. Libya has been torn by violence and division since long-time ruler, Muammar Gaddafi, was deposed and killed in 2011. --BBC--